ere unless I use training points on them.  Heh.<br>
<br>
As for your throwing, well, we mages *never* do good damage with it.  My record was 7 (I was *proud* of that 7, but that's not the point.  Heh).  But when you get in your low 20s you will be able to summon Throwing Daggers, which makes it very easy to train.  Plus, by the time you get that spell, you're high enough to be able to train it all the way up to the max of 75.<br>
<br>
So I guess what I'm saying is twofold:<br>
1) Don't get used to having a need for a melee attack button on your hot button window, you'll want to get rid of it later on (in your mid 20's, if you play like I do) for other things (I still use my pet commands down there, because the Pet Window doesn't have keyboard shortcuts for its buttons).<br>
<br>
2) Pick a single weapon skill, and stick with that one skill until you find you're taking too much of a beating being in melee.  We don't have the time typically to get many skills up there (unless you group, since you won't have to back out of melee so often to recover hp because others will have aggro over you), so you might as well specialize.  Unless you're the sort of person that likes seeing all of your skills maxed out, in which case you might want to max your Bind Wound skill as well.<br>
<br>
